#include<stdio.h>
void main()
{
int n;
printf("enter the number");
scanf("%d",&n);
printf("enter the number is",%d);
}

2.This file contains so-called function prototypes of functions such as printf() , scanf() , ... so that compiler knows what are their parameters and return values.



3.printf function is used to print the character, string, float, integer values onto the output screen.


4.main is the entry point of the program.


5.Variable is which we can change i.e., has no fixed values.


6.local variables and global variables


7. & operator is used to indicate the address of a variable.


8.%d refers to the integer. It is a format specifier.


9.Compilation of program means converting high level language into machine level language.


10.Running the program means executing the code as per the code is written.


11. Syntax error means not following the rule of declaring the function or missing important symbols.


12. Missing paranthesis, Missing commas,semicolons, writing wrong printf or scanf function.
